  "text": "However, current depth cameras are limited by manufacturing and physical constraints. Hence, depth images are affected by degenerations due to noise, missing values, and typically have a low resolution [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . To mitigate these problems, we need to recover the corresponding high-resolution (HR) depth image from a given low-resolution (LR) one.",
